commandDescription: Command for import the data extracted with data:export command into the project connected org
fileFlagDescription: Path to the exported file with data:export command for import into the auth org. Must be the -plan file
limitFlagDescription: Number of records to insert at one time. Max records per batch are 200. (200 by default)
sourceFlagDescription: Username or Alias to the source org for import data from the org, not from a file
queryFlagDescription: Query to extract data. You can use a simple query (Select [fields] from [object] [where] ...) or a complex query (select [fields], [query], [query] from [object] [where] ...) for export data in tree format
loadingRecordTypesMessage: Loading stored Record Types from target org
recordTypesLoadedMessage: Loading stored Record Types from target org
resolvingRecordTypeMessage: Resolving Record Type references on %s records
recordTypeError: DeveloperName not found on RecordType data. Please, put Recordtype.DeveloperName into the query to correct mapping of record types
recordTypeNotFoundError: The Record type %s not found on target org. Please, create the record type and then, import the data
recordTypeNotExistsError: Has no record types for %s on target org. Please, create record types and then, import the data
batchesCreatedMessage: Batches to insert data created. Total Records: %s ; Total Batches: %s
startInsertJobMessage: Start job to insert data. This operation can take several minutes. Please wait.
executeChildsInsertOperationMessage: Performing insert operation on %s child record(s)
errorsFoundMessage: Errors found on import, rolling back
rollbackFinishMessage: Roll back on %s record(s) finished succesfully
queryNotProvidedError: Wrong --query. Query are required to extract data from --source
notPlanFileError: Wrong --file path. Please, select a plan file (File ended with -plan.json)
startExtractingDataMessage: Start Extracting data from Org with username or alias %s
filesNotExistsMessage: The next files does not exists or do not has access permission: %s
importedSuccesfullyMessage: Data imported succesfully into your Auth Org
dataNotImportedMessage: Data does not import because found errors. Go to %s for see the errors by batch
examples: sfdx ah:data:export -q "Select Id, Name, BillingNumber, (Select Id, Name, AccountId, Phone from Contacts) from Account" -o "./export/accounts"
sfdx ah:data:export -q "Select Id, Name, BillingNumber, RecordType.DeveloperName from Account" -o "./export/accounts"
